<li class="commentbody" id="comment-124318">
			<cite><a href='http://eileendover.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Eileen Dover</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-124318" title="">July 29, 2008</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">15</div>

				<p>Oh. My. Word.</p>
<p>You see, I&#8217;m a lover of all things blueberry, and I think it started as a wee child and I hated Strawberry Shortcake (she was such a poser) but was in love with Blueberry Muffin. </p>
<p>It only became more of an intense love as I grew older when I learned how butter and cream made everything taste better&#8230; and well, I love anything with a crumb topping. Apples and crumbs. Apples and rhubarb and crumbs. Cookies and crumbs.</p>
<p>And blueberries and crumbs and ice-cream and comfy couch and a good movie and a summer night and an open door. Oh, and no interrupting phone calls.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
