<p>I HAVE made these with Tart Cherries and they are Phenomenal. Picked the cherries right off the trees, pitted and made this recipe to test them out. I omitted the lemon zest/juice, and subbed in 1 tsp almond extract in both the crumb base and the cherries, and used ~3/4 c of sugar. I took them to work (gleaning tart cherries for our food bank, actually) and they disappeared in minutes. Lots of thumbs up and compliments. I passed along your wonderful recipe and website to those who asked.</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
